%N A391210 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = Sum_{j=0..k} (-1)^j * binomial(k,j) * (3-j)^n.
%H A391210 Donald E. Knuth, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/math/9207222">Johann Faulhaber and Sums of Powers</a>, arXiv:math/9207222 [math.CA], 1992.
%H A391210 Petro Kolosov, <a href="https://github.com/kolosovpetro/SumsOfPowersViaBackwardFiniteDifferencesAndNewtonFormula/tree/main/mathematica">Mathematica programs</a>, GitHub, 2026.
%H A391210 Petro Kolosov, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18118011">Sums of powers via backward finite differences and Newton's formula</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%F A391210 T(n,k) = Sum_{j=k..n} binomial(2-k, j-k) * Stirling2(n, j) * j!.
%F A391210 T(n,k) = Sum_{j=0..n} E(n,j) * binomial(2+j-k, n-k), where E(n,j) is Eulerian number (Cf. A173018).
%F A391210 Let F(t, n, k) = Sum_{j=0..k} (-1)^j * binomial(k,j) * (t-j)^n,
%F A391210 then
%F A391210 F(0, n, k) = A278075(n,k),
%F A391210 F(1, n, k) = A389570(n,k),
%F A391210 F(2, n, k) = A391068(n,k),
%F A391210 F(3, n, k) = T(n,k) (this sequence).
%F A391210 Let S_m(n) be a sum of powers: S_m(n) = 1^m + 2^m + 3^m + ... + n^m, then
%F A391210 S_m(n) = Sum_{j=0..m} T(m,j) * ( (-1)^j*binomial(3,j+1) + binomial(n+j-3,j+1) ).
